snippet.textDisplay: The reason is that peanuts are probably the cheapest to grow. They aren't a true nut -- they're a legume, a bean. That means they're nitrogen fixers and effectively are their own fertilizer (which saves money), and they have much more rapid growth, allowing for Planters to pump out those pseudo-nuts into the gullible public's greedy maws. They skirt that line purely for the sake of reaping profits from unsuspecting nut-enthusiasts. Disgusting.
